  </sidebyside>

  <sidebyside widths="47% 47%" margins="0%">
    <stack>
      <p>
        To travel from Carl's home to the pet shop, he would go <m>3</m> blocks west, and then
        <m>2</m> blocks north.
      </p>
      <p>
        In the Cartesian coordinate system, the <em>positive</em> directions are to the
        <em>right</em> and <em>up</em>. The <em>negative</em> directions are to the <em>left</em>
        and <em>down</em>. So the pet shop's Cartesian coordinates are <m>(-3,2)</m>.
      </p>
    </stack>

